\cf4 Here are the first 20 pulse rates in our NHANES data set. This is the simplest plot you can construct of a set of numbers. It's called a stacked dot plot. Each value is plotted against the scale using a dot-- so each dot represents a person. This dot represents someone with a pulse rate of 54. Someone with rate of 56. And so on. When people have the same value, we stack them one above the other, so we can see how many there are. Hence, the "stacked" in stacked dot plot. Here we can see two people with a pulse rate of 70. And three with 74. Ignore the faded box shape at the bottom, for now.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\sa326\partightenfactor0
