\cf4 This plot shows an extreme case. The shape here is enormously skewed, squashed into what almost looks like a single spike near 0. It is showing total household incomes for the 2006 US Health and Retirement Survey. Household incomes go all the way up to $26 million. Next, we'll look more closely at the data squashed into the left-hand side of this plot. We've zoomed in on just the incomes up to $1 million. And we can see that nearly all household incomes are under about $300,000. Here we've zoomed in further-- to just the incomes up to $300,000. We're showing the median and the mean for the whole data set. There's a big difference between the two. The median is $43,000.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\sa326\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/data-to-insight/8/steps/508331#"}}{\fldrslt 
